      • Serialized Fields

        • stateA
          long stateA
          The first state; can be any long, as long as all states are not 0.
          This is a public field to match the style used by libGDX and to make changes easier.
        • stateB
          long stateB
          The second state; can be any long, as long as all states are not 0. This is the state that is scrambled and returned; if it is 0 before a number is generated, then the next number returned by RandomXMX256.nextLong() will be 0.
          This is a public field to match the style used by libGDX and to make changes easier.
